**Pseudocode for Backtracking Subset Sum Algorithm:**


function subsetSumBacktrack(set, target):
    result = []  // List to store all valid subsets
    currentSubset = []  // Current subset being explored
    index = 0  // Index to track position in the set

    function backtrack(index, currentSum):
        if currentSum == target:
            result.append(currentSubset.copy())  // Found a valid subset
            return
        if index >= len(set) or currentSum > target:
            return  // Prune: out of bounds or sum exceeds target

        // Include the current element
        currentSubset.append(set[index])
        backtrack(index + 1, currentSum + set[index])

        // Exclude the current element (backtrack)
        currentSubset.pop()
        backtrack(index + 1, currentSum)

    backtrack(0, 0)
    return result

