## Pseudocode for Rabin-Karp Algorithm

**Input:** Text $T$ of length $n$, pattern $P$ of length $m$, radix $d$, prime modulus $q$.

**Output:** All starting positions where $P$ occurs in $T$.


RabinKarp(T, P, d, q):
    n = length(T)
    m = length(P)
    h = d^(m-1) mod q  // Precompute the highest power
    p = 0  // Hash value for pattern
    t = 0  // Hash value for current text window

    // Compute initial hash values for pattern and first window of text
    for i = 0 to m-1:
        p = (d * p + val(P[i])) mod q
        t = (d * t + val(T[i])) mod q

    // Slide the pattern over text one by one
    for s = 0 to n-m:
        // Check if hash values match
        if p == t:
            // If hash matches, check characters directly
            if P[0..m-1] == T[s..s+m-1]:
                output "Pattern found at position" s

        // Compute hash for next window using rolling hash
        if s < n-m:
            t = (d * (t - val(T[s]) * h) + val(T[s+m])) mod q
            // Ensure t is non-negative
            if t < 0:
                t = t + q


